public interface RecyclingSupplier<T>

      • get

        @Nonnull
T get()
      throws ObjectCreationException,
             ObjectBorrowException,
             InterruptedException,
             TimeoutException
        block until a object is available and return it.
        Returns:
        - a object instance returned by this supplier.
        Throws:
        ObjectCreationException - - cannot create an object.
        ObjectBorrowException - - cannot borrow an object.
        InterruptedException - - interrupted.
        TimeoutException - - timed out while getting object.

      • recycle

        void recycle(T object,
           @Nullable
           Exception e)
        return a object previously borrowed from the pool, together with a optional exception in case one was encountered while using the object. passing an exception will cause the object to be validated and potentially retired from the pool.
        Parameters:
        object - - object to recycle.
        e - - exception encountered while handling the object. this is useful for the recycle to validate/retire object
